    "Various imaging and spectroscopic technologies have emerged as alternative methods to be used in the food industry for the sensory assessment of food items.",
    "In recent times, HSI technology has gained prime importance as a novel rapid and non-invasive technique for the sensory evaluation of foods (Liu et al., 2017).",
    "HSI is less time-consuming and a non-destructive technique to determine the sensory properties of a diverse range of food products.",
    "The VIS-NIR (400-1000 nm) HSI is the most used method for the evaluation of sensory attributes (Ozdogan et al., 2021).",
    "Table 5 summarises the recent studies done to evaluate the sensory properties of food products using the HSI technique."
